MODEL #PW9801L. GI model.  Includes original labeled box, papers, cleaning rod, extra springs and the key for the trigger locking device. Excellent condition. I have additional pictures I can email. 5 mags total. Never carried or holstered.

FTF OR SHIP TO YOUR FFL PLUS SHIPPING AND PRE-PAYMENT USPS MONEY ORDER. PREFER CCW HOLDERS FOR FTF MEET. ID REQUIRED. PLEASE INCLUDE YOUR NAME WHEN RESPONDING TO THIS AD. I ANSWER MESSAGES QUICKLY. I DO NOT RESPOND TO INQUIRIES OF 'DO YOU STILL HAVE THIS?' IF THIS AD IS UP THEN IT IS STILL AVAILABLE. INCLUDE YOUR PHONE NUMBER AND WE CAN TALK. 

Here is some additional info found on the web:
The Springfield Armory GI Micro Compact 1911 isn't actually a replica of the WWI and WWII pistols, as 1911 pistols this small weren't produced until late in the 1990's. However, the Micro Compact is an excellent carry pistol that also has a nostalgic feel to it.
The Micro Compact G.I. has a 3" barrel and a frame that's smaller than an Officer's size frame, giving it a weight of just 33 ounces, and making it ideal for carry.
The frame and slide are forged steel, and are parkerized. The 3" bull barrel is fully supported and ramped, and is also parkerized. Parkerizing gives the pistol a finish that's much tougher than anodizing.
The reddish-brown hardwood grips are stamped "U.S.", and contrast attractively with the black parkerized pistol. 
The sights on the pistol are original G.I. style, with a low profile notched rear sight and low rounded front sight blade.
The grip safety is flat, just like the old G.I. 1911's, as is the trigger. Trigger pull on the Micro Compact G.I. is five to six pounds, which is a good pull weight for a carry pistol.
The Micro Compact G.I. 1911 is a pistol with a lot of character, and one that can fit in the palm of your hand. It comes with a lifetime warranty that's good even if you're not the original purchaser.
Specifications
GI .45 3" Micro Compact PW9801LP  
 Caliber: .45 ACP  
 Capacity: 6+1  
 Barrel: 3" Fully supported and ramped barrel  
 Sights: Low-profile military  
 Sight Radius: 4.7"  
 Size: 33 oz., 6.5" overall length  
 Trigger Pull: 5 to 6 lbs.  
 Magazines: 1 

Every Springfield Armory 1911 pistol is equipped with a trigger locking device. A key inserted into a hole in the rear grip strap positively locks the trigger, making it impossible for a child to accidentally discharge the gun. This system gives you a choice as to whether or not you need to lock your gun. Unlike trigger locks on other brands of guns, the keyhole is small, so that it doesn't ruin the looks of the gun.

Vortex Viper PST Rifle Scope 1-4x24mm Illuminated TMCQ (MRAD) Reticle - Tactical Turrets

The Viper PST (Precision Shooting Tactical) riflescope boasts features associated with top-tier riflescopes, yet comes in at a street price under the $1,000 mark. Features
Extra-low dispersion (XD) glass increases resolution and color fidelity, resulting in crisp, sharp images.
Proprietary coatings increase light transmission with multiple anti-reflective coatings on all air-to-glass surfaces.
Second Focal Plane Reticle retains the same ideally-sized appearance at all magnification levels. Reticle sub-tensions used for estimating range, holdover and wind drift correction are accurate at the highest magnification.
Glass-etched Reticle is protected between two layers of glass for optimum durability and reliability.
Illuminated Reticle provides precise aiming under low-light conditions.
Waterproof, shockproof, and fog proof!
Precision force spring system for maximum repeatability and easy adjustment.
Precision glide erector system ensures smooth movement through the magnification range under the harshest conditions
MAG-View fiber optic inserts provide a highly visible reference for fast indentifcation of the magnification setting.
Radius bar fiber-optic insert on turrets provides a highly visible and tactile reference point for turret rotation.
Fast focus eye-piece!


AR-PEPR QD Scope Mount

The Burris AR-PEPR 30 millimeter Quick Detach Scope Mount with Picatinny Tops make it easy to gear up for different applications or shooting disciplines. The PEPR stands for Proper Eye Position Ready for combat. The ring bases are milled as a single, tough unit. The top of the rings feature the Picatinny rails for mounting additional accessories. postcontent:
I hate to do this, but I am selling my favorite rifle, an all original Mosin PU Sniper. I am saving for Air Force OTS and I have to let this go if I'm gonna keep my priorities in line. I bought this originally from classic firearms in October of 2013, back when you could still get them. This is an original PU Sniper, with the serial number of the scope stamped to the receiver of the rifle. I've fired it a handful of times since then and added a few extras onto it. I've added a reproduction scope cover, rubber butt pad, and aluminum shims for added accuracy and to lighten the trigger pull. All of these additions are obviously not permanent and I have all original hardware. This is consistently a 1.5-2.5 MOA gun and has always performed beautifully. I had plans of putting a timney trigger in a replacement stock and making this a fine hunting rifle. But, such is life. 

Optic: 1943 Progress 3.5 power scope. Force matched serial to the rifle. This scope was mated to the rifle at the armory and the serial number of the scope was stamped on the reciever. The glass is clear and the turrets are fully functional. The gross elevation adjustment screws are a little worn but they are locked in place. 
Stock: The stock is typical mosin fare. Stamped with numbers and letters all over. Visibly beat up with handling marks and dings. It is however straight and true. I have sanded down the fore-end to float the barrel and remove points of contact. 
Metal: The Blueing is 100%. The import marks are nicely tucked away on the underside of the barrel. 
Bore: The bore on this rifle is as good as any mosin is going to get. It looks as it did leaving the factory. Rifling is crisp and mirrored. Lands and grooves are sharp and bright as a brand new rifle. See Pictures. 

Along with the rifle I have 45 rds of conventional corrosive surplus, 28 rounds of LVE match grade brass case ammunition, two pouches with the original mosin cleaning kit, some targets, muffs, eyewear and targets. I even have the original box, wrapping, and manual the rifle came with. You really get a complete package with this. Feel free to text or email me with questions. postcontent:
Miami Shooters Club is hosting a NRA Basic Pistol Course next Sunday, May 24, at our facility at 1425 SW 107 Ave, Miami, FL 33174 - right across the street from FIU in the Publix Shopping Center. To register, click on this link: http://nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=317052

We have four spots still open.

This NRA Basic Pistol Shooting Course is being taught by my, Marcos Avellan, and I'm a certified NRA Instructor who has also trained under Navy Seal Jared Ogden and Green Beret Grady Powell (both as seen on National Geographic's Ultimate Survival Alaska)- and most recently I got to train with former Navy Seal Team 6 member Zak Jackson. This is an 8 hour course (includes range time) that teaches basic handgun knowledge (both for semi-automatics and revolvers), gun handling skills, shooting fundamentals, positions, gun maintenance and much more. 

The price of the course is only $125. There are no range fees - but ammo is not included. We provide guns at no charge.

To register, click on this link: http://nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=317052

Minimum age to attend the class is 13 years old and all minors must register along with a parent or legal guardian. You do not need any experience to take the course - and experienced shooters alike will learn from this course. You do NOT need to own a gun to participate, we do provide loaners pistols for those that need it.

Finishing the course also meets the state of Florida training requirements towards getting your concealed weapons permit (so you don't need to take a concealed weapons course after).

Lastly, if you have aspirations of being a NRA pistol instructor, this class is a prerequisite towards doing so.

For more information, please send an email right now to REDACTED with your name and phone number or call REDACTED.
